codex
Plan for the edits:
1. In `spacy_modal_codec.py`, add a narrow competing-scope bridge for `alethic -> conditional_normative` when conditional/statutory scope signals are present but conditional cues are absent.
2. Refine cross-family backfill thresholds so `deontic <-> temporal` and `deontic -> frame` get support at lower counts when strong scope evidence is present, while keeping existing high-threshold behavior for weaker evidence.
3. Strengthen `frame -> temporal` backfill in strong temporal contexts (calendar dates / temporal phrases) using scaled weights so date-heavy editorial/statutory text is less frame-dominated.
4. In `modal_registry.py` and scope phrases, add a few deterministic conditional-necessity phrases (`as may be necessary`, `to the extent necessary`) to reduce alethic overcapture in conditional statutory clauses.
5. Add focused unit tests in `tests/unit/optimizers/logic_theorem_optimizer/test_spacy_modal_codec.py` for these new cue/backfill behaviors and run only the affected tests.
